OL,3,COpen the door! First female Black Rod
OL,4,Cconfirms she's leaving Parliament
OL,6,FTraditionally, the door of the Commons
OL,7,Fis slammed in Black Rod's face to
OL,8,Fsymbolise the Commons' independence.
OL,9,FThey then bang three times on the door
OL,10,Fwith the staff. The door to the
OL,11,FCommons Chamber is then opened and all
OL,12,FMPs follow Black Rod back to the Lords
OL,13,FChamber to hear the Queen's Speech.
OL,15,FThe name Black Rod comes from the
OL,16,Fstaff the post-holder carries: an
OL,17,Febony staff of three and a half feet
OL,18,Ftopped with a golden lion. It is the
OL,19,Fmain symbol of the office's authority.
OL,20,FThe name Usher comes from the Latin
OL,21,Fussarius which means doorkeeper.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
