OL,6,FThe first reference to Black Rod in
OL,7,Fconnection with Parliament comes in a
OL,8,FGarter statute of 1522 which states
OL,9,Fthat Black Rod has an additional duty
OL,10,Fto "keep the doors... in the High
OL,11,FCourt called Parliament".
OL,13,FIt is thought that, when Henry VIII
OL,14,Fmoved from the Palace of Westminster
OL,15,Fto the Palace of Whitehall, Black Rod
OL,16,F- a member of the Royal Household,
OL,17,Fstayed behind to act as usher to the
OL,18,FHouse of Lords.
